# SPLUNK AI TOOLKIT + OLLAMA (GGUF, OFFLINE, PERSISTENT SETUP)

---

## 🧭 ARCHITECTURE

Splunk Search Head
↓
ollama_proxy (systemd service on Splunk)
↓
Ollama VM (GGUF model, offline)

---

## 🧱 PART 1 — OLLAMA VM (GGUF MODEL SETUP)

### STEP 1 — Install Ollama (on VM)

# (Linux example)

curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

Verify:
ollama --version

---

### STEP 2 — Add GGUF MODEL

Place your GGUF file on the VM, for example:
phi-3-mini.gguf

---

### STEP 3 — Create Modelfile

nano Modelfile

Contents:
FROM ./phi-3-mini.gguf

---

### STEP 4 — Create Model

ollama create phi3-local -f Modelfile

---

### STEP 5 — Run / Test Model

ollama run phi3-local

OR API test:
curl http://localhost:11434/api/generate 
-d '{
"model": "phi3-local",
"prompt": "test",
"stream": false
}'

---

### STEP 6 — Verify from Splunk Server

curl http://<OLLAMA_VM_IP>:11434/api/tags

Expected:
"phi3-local"

---

## 🧱 PART 2 — PROXY (ON SPLUNK SERVER)

### STEP 1 — Create Directory

mkdir -p /opt/ollama-proxy

---

### STEP 2 — Create Proxy File

nano /opt/ollama-proxy/ollama_proxy.py

---

### CONTENT

from flask import Flask, request, jsonify
import requests

app = Flask(**name**)

OLLAMA_URL = "http://<OLLAMA_VM_IP>:11434/api/generate"

@app.route("/")
def home():
return "Proxy is running"

@app.route("/v1/chat/completions", methods=["POST"])
def chat():
data = request.json

```
messages = data.get("messages", [])
prompt = messages[-1]["content"] if messages else ""

r = requests.post(OLLAMA_URL, json={
    "model": "phi3-local",
    "prompt": prompt,
    "stream": False,
    "options": {
        "num_predict": 200,
        "temperature": 0.2
    }
})

result = r.json()

return jsonify({
    "choices": [
        {
            "message": {
                "content": result.get("response", "")
            }
        }
    ]
})
```

app.run(host="127.0.0.1", port=5000)

